MAHA is not about politics- it’s about saving our younger generations.

We’re so grateful to CNN for highlighting the heart behind MAHA Girls— a movement that’s not about politics, trends, or outrage… it’s about helping Gen Z girls reclaim their health, one step at a time.

We’re not doctors or experts. We’re just 19-year-olds who got tired of watching our generation get sicker, sadder, and more disconnected — and decided to do something about it.

MAHA isn’t about being perfect. It’s about making real food cool again. Asking better questions. And reminding people that they don’t have to feel sick all of the time.

Thank you @cnn and @meenasaurus for seeing us, hearing us, and helping us share what this really means. This is just the beginning.
